    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1006"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.9421/48</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 677</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-28">January 28,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your despatch No. 1059 of
                    November 16, 1934,<note n="23" xml:id="d1006fn23">Not printed; for enclosed
                        memorandum of November 15, see <ref target="frus1934v03#pg_841">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 841</ref>.</note> there is herewith
                    transmitted a preliminary draft of a proposed consular convention with
                        Japan.<note n="24" xml:id="d1006fn24">Draft not printed.</note> This draft
                    was prepared in the Department on the basis of the existing Treaty with Poland,
                    signed at Washington in 1931,<note n="25" xml:id="d1006fn25">
                        <ref target="frus1931v02#pg_938">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1931, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 938</ref>.</note> and is in general
                    similar to other treaties concluded in recent years with Germany, Norway,
                    Finland, Cuba and other countries.</p>
                <p>This draft has not as yet received the approval of the Department and is
                    submitted to you at the present time for your confidential information and
                    study. It is requested that you examine the draft, referring the matter to the
                    Consul General, and report any suggestions or amendments that may appear
                    advisable.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
